### Wrapped Labels

Long labels will automatically wrap on tabs. If the label is too long for the tab, it will overflow and the text will not be visible.

{{""blazor"": ""Skclusive.Material.Docs.App.View.TabsWrappedLabel, Skclusive.Material.Docs.App.View""}}

### Disabled Tab

A Tab can be disabled by setting `disabled` property.

{{""blazor"": ""Skclusive.Material.Docs.App.View.DisabledTabs, Skclusive.Material.Docs.App.View""}}

## Fixed Tabs

Fixed tabs should be used with a limited number of tabs and when consistent placement will aid muscle memory.

### Full width

The `variant=""fullWidth""` property should be used for smaller views.
This demo also uses [react-swipeable-views](https://github.com/oliviertassinari/react-swipeable-views) to animate the Tab transition, and allowing tabs to be swiped on touch devices.

{{""blazor"": ""Skclusive.Material.Docs.App.View.FullWidthTabs, Skclusive.Material.Docs.App.View""}}

### Centered

The `centered` property should be used for larger views.

{{""blazor"": ""Skclusive.Material.Docs.App.View.CenteredTabs, Skclusive.Material.Docs.App.View""}}

